parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel pump failure can cause fuel leaks, leading to a fire hazard, and engine stalling, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel pump outlet connection

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel gauge malfunction can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to engine stalling, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
The lack of available replacement parts for the fuel system recall can cause delays in remediation, leaving drivers at risk of fuel leaks and engine stalling.
symptoms: Dealers unable to remedy the issue due to lack of parts
and drivers experiencing fuel leaks and engine stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump Failure - Cracked Outlet Flange
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracked outlet flange on the fuel pump can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, or leave the rider stranded.

The failure of the fuel sensor can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to incorrect fuel level readings, which can cause the rider to run out of fuel unexpectedly, potentially leading to accidents or leaving the rider stranded.
The failure of the fuel system can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, or leave the rider stranded.
The failure of the ABS pump motor can cause the loss of anti-lock braking system (ABS) functionality, leading to reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: ABS warning light on the dashboard
brake failure warning lamp on instrument cluster

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS module can cause the loss of anti-lock braking system (ABS) functionality, leading to reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: ABS warning light on the dashboard
error codes such as "005 DFO PUMP MOTOR VOLTAGE SUPPLY" and "009309 KOMBI UNDER TENSION".

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Final Drive Oil Leak onto Brake Rotor and Pads
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The oil leak from the final drive onto the brake rotor and pads can cause reduced braking performance, leading to increased stopping distances and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: oil on brake rotor and pads
possible lockup of rear wheel and loss of control.
